### âœ… ViewBag vs ViewData vs TempData (ASP.NET MVC / ASP.NET Core)

ViewData => Dictionary (`ViewDataDictionary`)
ViewBag => Dynamic Object
TempData => Dictionary 

used to send data from controller to view 
> ViewBag and ViewData are used to pass data from controller to view for a single request, while TempData is used to persist data across requests mainly during redirects.(return RedirectToAction()) here TempData is used .
---

# ğŸ”¹ Core Purpose

All three are used to **pass data from Controller to View**.

---

## âœ… Comparison Table (Must-remember)

| Feature            | ViewData                          | ViewBag              | TempData                         |
| ------------------ | --------------------------------- | -------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| Type               | Dictionary (`ViewDataDictionary`) | Dynamic Object       | Dictionary                       |
| Type Safety        | âŒ No                              | âŒ No                 | âŒ No                             |
| Lifetime           | Current Request Only              | Current Request Only | Across Requests                  |
| Scope              | Controller â†’ View                 | Controller â†’ View    | Controller â†’ View â†’ Next Request |
| Persistence        | Not stored                        | Not stored           | Stored in Session                |
| Needs Type Casting | âœ… Yes                             | âŒ No                 | âœ… Yes                            |
| Redirect Support   | âŒ No                              | âŒ No                 | âœ… Yes                            |

---

## âœ… ViewData

```csharp
ViewData["Name"] = "Onkar";
```

In View:

```cshtml
@ViewData["Name"]
```

* Uses key-value pair
* Requires casting for complex objects
* Works only for same request

---

## âœ… ViewBag

```csharp
ViewBag.Name = "Onkar";
```

In View:

```cshtml
@ViewBag.Name
```

* Wrapper over ViewData
* Uses dynamic
* Cleaner syntax

---

## âœ… TempData

```csharp
TempData["Message"] = "Saved Successfully";
```

In View:

```cshtml
@TempData["Message"]
```

* Persists across redirect
* Uses Session internally
* Best for success/error messages

---

# ğŸ”¥ Real Usage Example

### Controller

```csharp
public IActionResult Demo()
{
    ViewData["A"] = "From ViewData";
    ViewBag.B = "From ViewBag";
    TempData["C"] = "From TempData";

    return RedirectToAction("Result");
}
```

### Result Action

```csharp
public IActionResult Result()
{
    return View();
}
```

### View (Result.cshtml)

```html
<p>@ViewData["A"]</p>   <!-- âŒ null -->
<p>@ViewBag.B</p>       <!-- âŒ null -->
<p>@TempData["C"]</p>   <!-- âœ… works -->
```

